        <abstract> 
<p>Oswald Heer [in <hi rend="italic">Die Urwelt der Schweiz</hi> (1866)] agrees with CD that Swiss ants (<hi rend="italic">Formica sanguinea</hi>) capture more slaves than do British ants. Does this contradict selection, since the British ants are exposed to harder conditions and a poorer fauna?</p> 
        </abstract>
